  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bbf \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0ba8\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bbe \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bc8 - \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0 \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "No-confidence motion against Prime Minister Ranil if he does not step down - Freedom Party",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "Not only President Gotabaya Rajapaksa, but also Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe must resign.",
        "On the contrary, Sri Lanka Freedom Party General Secretary Dayasiri Jayasekara said that if the Prime Minister does not step down, steps will be taken to submit a no-confidence motion against him in Parliament.",
        "Due to people's protests, President Gotabaya Rajapaksa announced his resignation on Wednesday.",
        "However, due to the delay in handing over the resignation letter to the Speaker, massive demonstrations were held in many parts of the country including Colombo.",
        "A special party leader's meeting was held under the chairmanship of Speaker Mahinda Yaba Abeywardhana yesterday after the emergence of a restless situation in the country.",
        "Dayasiri Jayasekara mentioned the above while giving the position of the Freedom Party regarding the issues emphasized during the party leader's meeting and the current situation of the country. In this regard, he further informed,",
        "We have clearly emphasized that Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe should also resign in the party leader's meeting. Apart from that, we have also requested to convene the Parliament as soon as possible.",
        "Despite the continuous demands of Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe to step down by the demonstrators and the majority of the people of the country, if he does not listen to it, we will submit a motion of no confidence against him.",
        "That is why we have urged to convene Parliament immediately. We will also request the Speaker to submit a no-confidence motion against the Prime Minister in the Parliament soon and take it up for debate and vote on the same day. If the no-confidence motion is passed, he will lose the post of Prime Minister.",
        "The post of Acting President will also disappear. He said that we will continue to take action to remove both Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe and the President without a mandate from the people.",
        "However, in the meeting held between the cabinet members and Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe at the Prime Minister's Office last Monday, all the ministers who participated in the meeting agreed to hand over responsibilities to the government once an agreement is reached to form an all-party government.",
        "Accordingly, it is noteworthy that the Prime Minister's Office has informed the Acting President and Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe to Speaker Mahinda Yappa Abeywardena that the ruling party and the opposition should form an all-party government together and appoint a prime minister who can be accepted by the government and the opposition."
      ],
